{"post_content":"<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 1: High-level presentation on DevOps concepts (1 hour)<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Title<\/strong>: <strong>\"Exploring the DevOps Toolbox: Tools for Scalability, Deployment, and Incident Management\"<\/strong><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Objective<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Provide a high-level overview of essential DevOps tools, their purposes, and how they fit into the CI\/CD and operations ecosystem.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Content Outline<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>What is the DevOps Ecosystem?<\/strong><!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>A brief history of DevOps and the role of automation in modern workflows.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Key categories of DevOps tools: Infrastructure, CI\/CD, Observability, and Incident Management.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Popular Tools Developers Should Know<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Infrastructure as Code (IaC)<\/strong>: Terraform, Ansible.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Containerization and Orchestration<\/strong>: Docker, Kubernetes, Helm.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Deployment Automation<\/strong>: ArgoCD (GitOps for Kubernetes).<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Monitoring and Alerts<\/strong>: Prometheus, Grafana, Opsgenie.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Real-World Integration<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>How tools like Helm and ArgoCD work together for Kubernetes deployments.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Using Opsgenie for proactive incident response.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 1: Foundations of CI\/CD Pipelines (5 hours)<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Key Topics<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Introduction to CI\/CD.<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Benefits of CI\/CD and its role in software delivery.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>GitLab overview and pipeline architecture.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Designing efficient pipelines with stages, jobs, and runners.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Managing build stages, jobs, and runners.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Introduction to securing CI\/CD pipelines:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Managing secrets and environment variables securely (e.g., GitLab CI\/CD secrets).<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Implementing access controls and audit logs for GitLab projects (RBAC).<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Hands-On Lab (paired)<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Create and deploy a simple CI\/CD pipeline in GitLab.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Automate a sample application build and test.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Secure the pipeline using GitLab\u2019s built-in secret management and RBAC features.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 2: High-level presentation on DevOps concepts (1 hour)<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Title<\/strong>: <strong>\"GitOps, Branching Strategies, and Repository Design for Scale\"<\/strong><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Objective<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Introduce developers to effective branching strategies, GitOps principles, and the pros and cons of monorepo vs. multirepo setups.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Content Outline<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Branching Strategies for teams<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Overview of popular branching models:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>GitFlow, Trunk-based Development, and Release Branching.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>How to choose a strategy for your team size and release cycle.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Introduction to GitOps<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>What is GitOps, and why is it important?<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Git as the single source of truth for infrastructure and deployments.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Tooling examples: Flux, ArgoCD.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Monorepo vs. Multirepo<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Monorepo<\/strong>: Advantages (simplified dependency management, single source of truth) and challenges (scalability, complexity).<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Multirepo<\/strong>: Advantages (independence, faster builds) and challenges (dependency tracking, fragmentation).<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>When to choose each approach.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ol>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 2: Monitoring and Observability (5 hours)<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Key Topics<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Monitoring principles and the \"Three Pillars of Observability\" (metrics, logs, and traces).<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Setting up Prometheus for pipeline and system metrics collection.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Visualizing metrics with Grafana dashboards.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Creating and analyzing dashboards for system health.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Incident response workflows.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Security logging essentials:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Identifying suspicious activities in logs (e.g., unauthorized access attempts).<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Correlating logs for security incident detection.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Proactive alerting for pipeline issues and potential security threats.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Hands-On Lab (paired)<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Integrate Prometheus and Grafana with GitLab to monitor pipeline performance.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Build dashboards to monitor CI\/CD pipeline performance.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Configure security logging to detect and analyze failed login attempts and unauthorized changes.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Tools used<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Prometheus:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Open-source metrics and monitoring tool.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Used to collect and store real-time metrics such as system performance and pipeline health.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Grafana:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Visualization tool integrated with Prometheus for building and customizing dashboards.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enables participants to create real-time visual insights into pipeline metrics.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>GitLab\u2019s Built-in Monitoring Features:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Exploring the monitoring and analytics capabilities provided directly within GitLab, such as pipeline insights, job statistics and historical DORA metrics.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 3: High-level presentation on DevOps concepts (1 hour)<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p><strong>Title<\/strong>: <strong>\"Smart Deployments: Canary Releases, A\/B Testing, and Rollbacks\"<\/strong><\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Objective<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:paragraph -->\n<p>Teach developers about deployment strategies that minimize risk, maximize user feedback, and ensure smooth rollbacks when failures occur.<\/p>\n<!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Content Outline<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list {\"ordered\":true} -->\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Modern Deployment Strategies<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Canary Deployments<\/strong>: Gradually rolling out changes to a small user subset.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Blue\/Green Deployments<\/strong>: Seamlessly switching between environments for zero downtime.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>A\/B Testing<\/strong>: Testing variations in production to gather user behavior data.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Failure Recovery Techniques<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Importance of monitoring during deployments (using tools like Prometheus and Grafana).<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Automated rollbacks and the role of health checks.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Real-World Examples<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>How big tech companies like Google or Netflix implement these strategies.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Simpler versions of these strategies for small teams.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ol>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->\n\n<!-- wp:heading {\"level\":4} -->\n<h4 class=\"wp-block-heading\"><strong>Day 3: Logging and Advanced Practices (5 hours)<\/strong><\/h4>\n<!-- \/wp:heading -->\n\n<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Key Topics<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Centralized Logging for CI\/CD Pipelines:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Setting up ELK (Elasticsearch, Logstash, Kibana) for log aggregation.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Troubleshooting pipeline and application issues using centralized logs.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Enhancing CI\/CD Pipelines:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Implementing automated rollbacks and canary deployments.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Continuous improvement of pipeline performance and security.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Security Testing in Pipelines:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Introduction to SAST (Static Application Security Testing).<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Running DAST (Dynamic Application Security Testing) on deployed applications.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Analyzing and remediating vulnerabilities in SAST and DAST reports.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Incident response workflows and case studies.<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Best practices for responding to and mitigating security incidents.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li><strong>Hands-On Lab (paired)<\/strong>:<!-- wp:list -->\n<ul class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Configure centralized logging for GitLab pipelines.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Simulate and troubleshoot common CI\/CD pipeline issues.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\n\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\n<li>Integrate GitLab SAST and DAST scans to identify and fix vulnerabilities in the code.<\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list --><\/li>\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><\/ul>\n<!-- \/wp:list -->","post_type":"training","post_status":"publish","post_name":"ci-cd-essentials","post_title":"CI\/CD Essentials","post_password":"","post_date":"2025-02-21 16:43:52","post_date_gmt":"2025-02-21 16:43:52","post_excerpt":"This hands-on course introduces participants to modern DevOps practices, focusing on building efficient and secure CI\/CD pipelines, implementing robust monitoring, and leveraging logging tools to optimize application delivery. Designed for an audience eager to enhance their DevOps expertise, the training uses GitLab as the technical environment. With a mix of theory, demonstrations, and interactive labs, attendees will gain practical insights into creating scalable, reliable workflows aligned with industry best practices.","post_parent":null,"author":"admin","meta":{"_aioseo_description":[null],"_aioseo_keywords":["a:0:{}"],"_aioseo_og_article_section":[""],"_aioseo_og_article_tags":["a:0:{}"],"_aioseo_og_description":[null],"_aioseo_og_title":[null],"_aioseo_title":[null],"_aioseo_twitter_description":[null],"_aioseo_twitter_title":[null],"_edit_last":"admin","_wp_old_slug":["devops-best-practices-to-build-ci-cd-pipelines-monitoring-and-logging","building-and-monitoring-ci-cd-pipelines"],"audience":["<p>This course is designed for developers with limited DevOps experience who want to expand their understanding of CI\/CD pipelines, monitoring, and security practices.<\/p>"],"duration":["3 days"],"languages":["English or French"],"maxparticipants":["8"],"minparticipants":["2"],"outcomes":["<p><!-- wp:paragraph --><\/p>\r\n<p>By the end of this course, participants will be able to:<\/p>\r\n<p><!-- \/wp:paragraph -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list --><\/p>\r\n<ol class=\"wp-block-list\"><!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li>Design and implement efficient and secure CI\/CD pipelines using GitLab.<\/li>\r\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li>Deploy monitoring and logging solutions to enhance deployment reliability.<\/li>\r\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li>Integrate security practices into DevOps workflows, addressing risks and vulnerabilities.<\/li>\r\n<!-- \/wp:list-item -->\r\n\r\n<!-- wp:list-item -->\r\n<li>Apply DevOps best practices to address real-world challenges.<\/li>\r\n<!-- \/wp:list-item --><